Hence, $z_2 = \operatorname{cis} (0) = 1,$ so $|z_2|^2 = 1,$ up to a $90^\circ$ shift.  But $|z_3|^2 = 9,$ so $|z_3| = 3,$ as given.  Hence, $3 \operatorname{cis} (\theta_3) = 3,$ so $z_3 = 3$ and $\theta_3 = \boxed{0}.$

To summarize, $z_1 = \operatorname{cis} (90^\circ),$ $z_2 = 1,$ and $z_3 = 3.$  Therefore,
\[|z_1 + z_2 + z_3| = |\operatorname{cis} (90^\circ) + 1 + 3| = |\operatorname{cis} (90^\circ) + 4| = |\operatorname{cis} (- \frac{\pi}{2}) + (-4i)|,\]so
\[|z_1 + z_2 + z_3| = | -4 - 4i| = \sqrt{48} = 4\sqrt{3}.\]

