The given line segment forms a chord of a circle with length $2\sqrt{35},$ and lengthening this chord to a major arc forms the curve described by $S.$  The radius of the circle is $r = \frac{\sqrt{35}}{6},$ so the central angle of the minor arc of length $2\sqrt{35} \approx 9.192$ has measure
\[\frac{2\sqrt{35}}{2 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{35}}{6}} = 6.\]Hence, the minor arc is an arc of a circle with angle measure $6^\circ.$

Thus, the area of the region inside the curve $S$ is
\[\frac{6}{360} \cdot \pi \cdot \left( \frac{\sqrt{35}}{6} \right)^2 = \pi \cdot \frac{35}{1296} = \pi \cdot \frac{5\cdot 7}{2^7} = \pi \cdot \frac{35}{128} = \boxed{\frac{35\pi}{128}}.\]The answer is: \frac{35\pi}{128}

