From $\triangle PAQ \sim \triangle AQD$, $\frac{QD}{AQ} = \frac{PA}{AD}$.  By Pythagoras, $QD = 25 \cdot \sqrt{1 - \frac{1}{16}} = 25 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{15}}{4}$.  Therefore, $QH-HD = 25 - 25 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{15}}{4} = \frac{25}{4}(4 - \sqrt{15})$, so $QR-RD = \frac{25}{4}(4 - \sqrt{15})$.

