Let's start by multiplying both sides of the equation by $(x + 2)(x + 3)(x + 8)(x + 9)$. This will eliminate the denominators on both sides.

$(x + 1)(x + 3)(x + 8)(x + 9) + (x + 8)(x + 2)(x + 3) = (x + 2)(x + 3)(x + 8) + (x + 7)(x + 2)(x + 9)$.

Next, let's expand the expressions on both sides of the equation.

